SIMPLE: inducement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inducement
<hw>In*duce"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Induce</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inducing, or the state of being
induced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which induces; a motive or consideration that
leads one to action or induces one to act; <as>as, reward is an
<ex>inducement</ex> to toil</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Mark the
<xex>inducement</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Matter stated by way of explanatory
preamble or introduction to the main allegations of a pleading; a
leading to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Motive; reason; influence. See
<er>Motive</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inducer</ent>⟦br⟧
